<item>
            <title>[LU-19837] Compatibility updates for kernel v6.19</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19837</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Linux commit v6.18-rc1-6-ge12d203b8c880&lt;br/&gt;
  vfs: allow mkdir to wait for delegation break on parent&lt;br/&gt;
Provide a compatible vfs_mkdir for older kernels&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Linux commit v6.18-rc1-7-gd8753f788ab49&lt;br/&gt;
  fs: provide accessors for -&amp;gt;i_state&lt;br/&gt;
Provide a compatible inode_state_read() for older kernels&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Linux commit v6.18-rc1-10-gc826229c6a82f&lt;br/&gt;
  vfs: make vfs_create break delegations on parent directory&lt;br/&gt;
Provide a compatible vfs_create for older kernels&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Linux commit v6.18-rc1-18-gb37491d72b43c&lt;br/&gt;
  interval_tree: Fix ITSTATIC usage for *_subtree_search()&lt;br/&gt;
Provide an alternate configure test for INTERVAL_TREE_DEFINE&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Linux commit v6.18-rc1-20-ga27628f436343&lt;br/&gt;
  fs: rework I_NEW handling to operate without fences&lt;br/&gt;
Provide a compatible ilookup5_nowait for older kernels&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Linux commit v6.18-rc2-1-g70e0a80a1f358&lt;br/&gt;
  treewide: Remove in_irq()&lt;br/&gt;
Use in_hardirq() directly&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Linux commit v6.18-rc3-603-gbf33247a90d3e&lt;br/&gt;
  net: Add struct sockaddr_unsized for sockaddr of unknown length&lt;br/&gt;
Provide a mapping of sockaddr_unsized to sockaddr for older kernels&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Linux commit v6.18-rc5-51-gfc45aee662232&lt;br/&gt;
  get rid of kill_litter_super()&lt;br/&gt;
Use kill_anon_super() when kill_litter_super() not available&lt;/p&gt;</description>
